ace-time\nboundary can be used to reconstruct the directionality of one-electron\ncandidate events, allowing for further $^8$B background suppression due to the\ncorrelation between the direction of the scattered electron and the position of\nthe sun. We find polar and azimuthal angular resolutions of 0.46 and 0.84\nradians respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Feb 2019 06:17:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-20"}
